    <textstream>
      <p>
        <s t="t1">
          <ot>You must study to be frank with the world: frankness is the child of honesty and courage.    By Robert E. Lee</ot>
          <tt>在世间必须学会以真诚示人：率真乃是诚实与勇敢之子。    ——罗比特·E·李</tt>
          <wd v="4">
            <w>
              <txt>be frank with</txt>
              <pro></pro>
              <pos></pos>
              <def>对……坦白、直率</def>
            </w>
            <w>
              <txt>courage</txt>
              <pro>[ˈkʌridʒ]</pro>
              <pos></pos>
              <def>n.勇气，胆量</def>
            </w>
          </wd>
        </s>
        <s t="t1">
          <ot>Turn your wounds into wisdom.    By Oprah Winfrey</ot>
          <tt>把你的伤口转变为智慧。    ——奥普拉·温弗瑞</tt>
          <wd v="4">
            <w>
              <txt>turn...into...</txt>
              <pro></pro>
              <pos></pos>
              <def>把……变成……</def>
              <clon>
                <c>turn</c>
                <c>into</c>
              </clon>
            </w>
            <w>
              <txt>wound</txt>
              <pro>[wu:nd]</pro>
              <pos></pos>
              <def> n.创伤，伤口 vt.使受伤，伤害</def>
              <clon>
                <c>wounds</c>
              </clon>
            </w>
          </wd>
        </s>
        <s t="t1">
          <ot>A good head and a good heart are always a formidable combination.   By Nelson Mandela</ot>
          <tt>聪明的头脑和高尚的心灵永远是最强大的结合。    ——纳尔逊·曼德拉</tt>
          <wd v="4">
            <w>
              <txt>formidable</txt>
              <pro>['fɔ:midəbl]</pro>
              <pos></pos>
              <def>adj. 强大的，可怕的，难对付的</def>
            </w>
            <w>
              <txt>combination</txt>
              <pro>[ˌkɔmbiˈneiʃən]</pro>
              <pos></pos>
              <def> n.结合(体)，联合(体)，化合</def>
            </w>
          </wd>
        </s>
        <s t="t1">
          <ot>The truest wisdom is a resolute determination.     By Napoleon Bonaparte</ot>
          <tt>最真正的智慧在于有一个坚定的决心。    ——拿破仑·波拿巴</tt>
          <wd v="4">
            <w>
              <txt>resolute</txt>
              <pro>[ˈrezəlu:t]</pro>
              <pos></pos>
              <def>a.坚决的</def>
            </w>
            <w>
              <txt>determination</txt>
              <pro>[diˌtə:miˈneiʃən]</pro>
              <pos></pos>
              <def>n.决心，决定；确定，测定</def>
            </w>
          </wd>
        </s>
        <s t="t1">
          <ot>Honesty is the first chapter in the book of wisdom.    By Thomas Jefferson</ot>
          <tt>诚实是智慧之书的第一章。    ——托马斯·杰斐逊</tt>
          <wd v="4">
            <w>
              <txt>honesty</txt>
              <pro>['ɔnisti]</pro>
              <pos></pos>
              <def> n.诚实, 正直</def>
            </w>
            <w>
              <txt>chapter</txt>
              <pro>[ˈtʃæptə]</pro>
              <pos></pos>
              <def>n.章，回，篇</def>
            </w>
          </wd>
        </s>
      </p>
